-- Norway's oil fund buys logistics properties in Spain
-- 
-- Tue Sep 02, 2014 09:57AM EDT
-- None



OSLO, Sept 2 (Reuters) - Norway's sovereign wealth fund has acquired a 50 percent stake in a series of Spanish logistics properties for 242 million euros ($317.6 mln) through its joint venture with Prologis <PLD.N>, the fund said on Tuesday.

The deal includes eight buildings with a total leasable area in excess of 150,000 square meters and two land parcels totaling 14.9 hectares in Madrid and Barcelona, it added.